French budget minister: 'France cannot go an entire year without a budget'
description: With the French government at risk of collapsing, Amélie de Montchalin says in an interview that the deadline to submit a draft budget to the Assemblée Nationale is October 13. Any later and a special law would be required to avoid a shutdown, which she sees as a problematic last resort.

Afghanistan earthquake rescue efforts slowed by lack of resources
description: The earthquake that struck near Jalalabad, in eastern Afghanistan, overnight from Sunday to Monday has left more than 1,400 people dead and 3,000 injured. The difficulty in accessing some remote valleys and the shortcomings of the Taliban regime have raised fears of an even higher death toll.

headline: Italy retorts after 'fiscal dumping' remarks by French MP Bayrou revive tensions
description: The French prime minister's comments regarding Italian tax policy for the ultra-wealthy sparked outrage in Italy on Sunday, including from Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, who emphasized the stability of her government.

headline: Venice Film Festival: Julia Roberts shines in Luca Guadagnino's 'After the Hunt'
description: The American actress plays a woman torn between ambition and principle in this film, presented out of competition, which examines morality and ethics in the wake of #MeToo.

headline: Thomas Piketty: 'To succeed in the climate transition, we must redistribute wealth differently'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the French economist explains that protecting the planet from climate change cannot be achieved without reducing inequality.

description: Repeated attacks on the central bank, meant to force it to lower interest rates, in defiance of economic data, threaten financial stability. Disregarding reality for political convenience can have dramatic consequences, writes Le Monde columnist Stéphane Lauer.

headline: The discreet rise of facial recognition around the world
description: Driven by artificial intelligence and backed by some political leaders as well as private companies, this highly sensitive technology is becoming commonplace in many countries and is making inroads across Europe.
